*[[Rock Plaza Central]], an indie rock band favored by [[Pitchfork Media]], gained attention for their radically different cover of the song, with brass-and-banjo roots-rock stylings.<ref>{{cite news|first=Brad|last=Wheeler|title=Too sexy for their suits|url=http://www.theglobeandmail.com/servlet/story/LAC.20070130.ROCK30/TPStory/TPEntertainment/Music/|work=The Globe and Mail|date=2007-01-30|accessdate=2007-01-30}}</ref>
*"SexyBack" was released as a promotional single and a bonus track on the [[Wal-Mart]] version of the 2007 cover album ''[[Poison'd!]]'' by American [[rock (music)|rock]] band [[Poison (band)|Poison]].<ref>{{cite journal|first=Gary|last=Graff|title=Poison bandmates end tensions with new album of cover songs|date=2007-06-22|work=[[The Plain Dealer (newspaper)|The Plain Dealer]]|page=T15|quote=Poison also laid down a take of Justin Timberlake's "Sexyback" which appears on special editions of "Poison 'd"}}</ref>
*British soul singer [[Corinne Bailey Rae]] recorded a jazz/swing version whilst appearing on [[BBC Radio 1]]'s [[Live Lounge]] in 2007.<ref>{{cite journal|first=Stephen|last=Dalton|title=Web video of the day&nbsp;<U+2014> Viewing Guide|date=2007-08-17|work=[[The Times]]|page=Times2 23}}</ref>

